720.question: How much is proposed model better than baselines in performed experiments?
720.response: {'Answer': 'The proposed GDP model outperforms baselines E2ECM and CDM in all evaluation metrics on both datasets. Compared with E2ECM, the proposed GDP model reduces 64.5% parameters and 31.5% dialogue policy parameters on average. Compared with CDM, the proposed GDP model reduces 67.6% parameters and 91.3% dialogue policy parameters on average.'}
720.answer:
most of the models have similar performance on BPRA: DSTC2 (+0.0015), Maluuba (+0.0729)
GDP achieves the best performance in APRA: DSTC2 (+0.2893), Maluuba (+0.2896)
GDP significantly outperforms the baselines on BLEU: DSTC2 (+0.0791), Maluuba (+0.0492)
